events.name: San Gabriel Mountains Trailbuilders
events.description: The San Gabriel Mountains Trailbuilders work the 1st, 3rd, and 5th Saturday of every month, and we work special projects which are not scheduled. Please email us to get on to the mailinglist to keep informed about scheduled and special projects! Email Ben atbwootenwhite@hotmail.com

events.description: Beginners welcome. The group meets every other Saturday at 8AM in Altadena. See here for more details https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10c0f4aabae2ba4ffc61-volunteer2

events.name: Clean up of HWY 39!
events.description:
Dear friends of Azusa Beautiful,




We hope to see you this Saturday, July 22 from 8 am to 10 am.  We'll be picking up litter along Hwy 39, which also aligns with the bike trail. We'll be meeting at the bike trail parking lot, and supplies will be provided. Please note that volunteers must be 16 years or older to participate in this project.  NOTE:  We are meeting at 8 am to beat the summer heat! 

Please invite your friends and family to join us and help keep our community beautiful!  

Thank you for your willingness to help! We appreciate your support and look forward to seeing you on Saturday!   

Please respond to this email if you plan on attending. 

Sincerely,

Maricela Cueva
Azusa Beautiful
(626) 224-0778
